        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "For reference, I tried checking the terminfo and behavior for a few terminals:\n\n| Terminal  | Se Sequence | Terminal Default Style | `\\E[0 q` Behavior                        |\n| :---      | :---        | :---                   | :---                                     |\n| Alacritty | `\\E[0 q`    | Steady Block           | Resets to user configured default        |\n| Ghostty   | `\\E[2 q`    | Blinking Block         | Resets to user configured default        |\n| st        | `\\E[2 q`    | Steady Block           | Steady block (which is compiled default) |\n| Kitty     | `\\E[2 q`    | Blinking Block         | Resets to user configured default        |\n| WezTerm   | `\\E[2 q`    | Steady Block           | Resets to user configured default        |\n\nIMO, Alacritty is the only one that gets it right here. I think these terminals have `\\E[2 q` as the `Se` sequence because steady block is default in older terminals, but for a lot of them, it doesn't even line up with their own default out of the box. All the terminals I tried worked like I'd expect when I used `\\E[0 q` to reset to the default, but I know there are a lot more terminals out there than the ones I tested.\n\nNote: `\\E[2 q` sets steady block, and `\\E[0 q` is supposed to set default. [Ghostty docs](https://ghostty.org/docs/vt/csi/decscusr).\n\nEdit: The `Se` terminfo extension originates from xterm, and is explained on [this page](https://invisible-island.net/xterm/terminfo.html). It says,\n\n> Se resets the cursor style to the terminal power-on default.\n\nTo me, there's some ambiguity in that, but the sensible thing seems to be setting the \"power-on default\" that's specified in the user config, in which case only Alacritty defined it properly among the terminals I tested. The other interpretation would be the power-on default with no config, but I don't know why a program would want to use that.\n\nThis could mostly be fixed by updating `patch_terminfo_bugs` to change the sequence for popular terminals to `\\E[0 q`.",
