            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "\n> because 95% of users like the 'guicursor' default, and it's obviously better, despite your personal tastes?\n\nThat is opinionated. \n\nIt is a bug that the cursor is altered and not reset to its default style. If the cursor cannot be reliable set and reset it shall not be default to alter it? That the switch to prevent the issue is now buggy is adding on top.\n\nPS: The default cursor shape of the Linux Terminal is *underline*. Interestingly nvim resets the cursor shape of the Linux terminal (other than libvte) but alters its color on exit 🫣\n\n",
