        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@kalken Try changing your `$TERM` to `iterm2`. nvim actually patches the sequence needed for iTerm2 if you have a proper `$TERM`. Although MacOS doesn't even have an entry for `iterm2`, so perhaps `iterm` would work better for you. iTerm2 fixed their terminfo for resetting cursor style, but I've got no idea when that might actually propagate to MacOS - probably years. I wouldn't hold my breath.\n\n@flaphoschi Those most likely work if your `$TERM` is set to `gnome`. I don't know what `$TERM` they use by default, but terminals like to lie, so they're probably `xterm-256color`.\n\nSolving this may be a bit easier once https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39555 is merged. Currently, your options are to set `$TERM` to one that's been patched for this issue, or to compile a new terminfo entry for the `$TERM` you use with the correct sequence for `Se`.",
            "created_at": "2026-05-11T22:30:23Z",
